\cf0\f0 I took a step back with my own simple multiplicative hash, which multiplies the ASCII values of all characters. Although this had been discussed in help lab I didn't implement it at first, because I thought the math involved might take a meaningfully longer time, an assumption that seems to be incorrect based on the results. Crucially, I also realised at this point that all hash methods potentially returning keys greater than the table size are more effective when the table is a prime number in size, so I did that.\cf1\f1\par
